Richard Vidutis: I think he really set strict goals. He kept tabs on people that, were transcribing, and…

54
00:04:51.690 --> 00:04:55.300
Richard Vidutis: On the field workers, what they were doing, where they were going.

55
00:04:55.790 --> 00:05:01.729
Richard Vidutis: I guess there was… even though they had a lot of money, still.

56
00:05:02.740 --> 00:05:09.560
Richard Vidutis: There was budget concerns, time concerns, So, he kept…

57
00:05:10.380 --> 00:05:15.680
Richard Vidutis: He kept on top of all of that, it was demanding.

58
00:05:16.870 --> 00:05:22.220
Richard Vidutis: It's smile, but you know that It was tough.

59
00:05:23.550 --> 00:05:30.810
Richard Vidutis: So… Either played with him, or you stayed away from him, it's just… Wait, bro.

60
00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:38.590
Julie Stout: What traits best capture Dawson as a person?

